The Queen and Princess Margaret recorded a special tape of favourite children 's songs for the Queen Mother 's 90th birthday in 1990 .
Pianist Laurie Holloway was invited to Buckingham Palace by Princess Margaret to accompany herself and The Queen for the performance which was recorded on a cassette tape .
The Royals recorded songs such as I know Where The Flies Go In Winter Time .
The Queen Mother enjoyed a drink of gin at 11 am .